aims-os-math (2.1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Slim split for v2.1. The Regular-track baseline now keeps only
    what every AIMS student touches: the SciPy ecosystem, classic
    Jupyter, R base, gnuplot-qt, gdb / valgrind, the OpenBLAS / LAPACK
    / FFTW dev headers, black + mypy, sqlite3, and a French-only
    TeX Live (texlive base + latex-extra + fonts-extra + lang-french
    + pictures + biber + latexmk + dvipng). About 1.2 GB on disk
    instead of ~2.5 GB.
  * Move the v2.0 extras to aims-os-math-extras:
    + Maxima + wxMaxima
    + Full Octave (symbolic / statistics / optim / control / signal)
    + R tidyverse (r-recommended, tidyverse, ggplot2, dplyr, knitr,
      rmarkdown)
    + Multilingual TeX Live (English, other-languages including
      African hyphenation, Arabic, publishers, science, XeTeX,
      LuaTeX, bibtex-extra, TeXstudio)
    + GeoGebra, gnuplot-doc
    + Niche Python: mpi4py (HPC), biopython, skimage, igraph, rpy2,
      tables, pygments, reportlab
    + libhdf5-dev, libgmp-dev, libmpfr-dev
  * Adds Breaks: aims-os-math (<< 2.1) so the v2.0 -> v2.1 upgrade
    is handled cleanly. To restore the full stack:
    `apt install aims-os-math-extras` (or `aims-os-everything`).

