aims-os-math (2.0+4) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Refactor for AIMS filière structure: split the Big Data / NLP /
    Computer Vision / Climate / Database stack into aims-os-bigdata,
    and the cryptography / ethical-hacking / forensics stack into
    aims-os-security. Both new metapackages Depend on aims-os-math,
    so the AIMS OS ISO (which installs all three) gets the same set
    of packages as before — no functional regression for installed
    systems. The split makes the AIMS apt repo more useful for
    standalone installs: a Regular-track student can apt-install
    aims-os-math alone, a Coop Big Data student gets the Big Data
    layer via aims-os-bigdata, a Coop Security student gets the
    security layer via aims-os-security.
  * Update Description to reflect the new scope.

