    + ruff (fast Rust linter — not in Trixie main) is installed
      system-wide via pipx in chroot hook 0100-pipx-tools.

 -- AIMS Senegal IT <hakim@aims-senegal.org>  Sat, 23 May 2026 09:00:00 +0000

aims-os-math (2.0+2) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix install failure in v2.0+1: 7 of the curriculum-driven additions
    turned out not to be packaged in Trixie main. packages.debian.org
    returns HTTP 200 even for "Package not available in this suite"
    error pages, so the first compatibility check was a false positive.
    + Drop from Depends (install on demand via pipx/mamba):
      python3-pyarrow, python3-polars, python3-duckdb, python3-spacy,
      python3-gensim, python3-transformers, python3-pyfftw.
    + Replace texlive-lang-african → texlive-lang-other. The
      standalone African languages texlive package never existed
      in any Debian suite (verified via packages.debian.org search);
      texlive-lang-other is Trixie's "everything else" texlive
      language meta-package and covers Wolof, Swahili, Amharic,
      Hausa and Twi hyphenation patterns.
    + Update Description and add inline NOTE comments pointing
      students at the install-on-demand path.

 -- AIMS Senegal IT <hakim@aims-senegal.org>  Fri, 22 May 2026 08:00:00 +0000

aims-os-math (2.0+1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Align package set with the 2025-2026 AIMS curriculum (45 courses).
    + Big Data / data engineering (Data Mining and Big Data Analytics,
      Case Study from Industries in Big Data, High Dimensional Data
      Analysis): python3-dask, python3-distributed, python3-pyarrow,
      python3-polars, python3-duckdb.
    + NLP & Generative AI (Natural Language Processing, Generative AI):
      python3-nltk, python3-spacy, python3-gensim, python3-transformers.
    + Computer Vision (Computer Vision course): python3-opencv on top
      of the scikit-image already shipped.
    + Climate sciences (Climate Dynamic, Mathematical Methods for
      Climate): python3-xarray, python3-netcdf4, python3-cartopy.
    + Crypto primitives for the Post Quantum Cryptography course:
      python3-cryptography, python3-pycryptodome. Qiskit deliberately
      not shipped — `pipx install qiskit` for the latest upstream.
    + Ethical Hacking, Computer Security 1, Mathematical Model for
      Network Security, Auditing Computer Forensics: nmap, wireshark,
      tcpdump, john, hashcat, aircrack-ng, sleuthkit, foremost,
      binwalk, python3-scapy.
    + Database course: postgresql-client, mariadb-client, redis-tools,
      python3-psycopg2, python3-pymongo (clients only — labs use
      remote DB hosts).
    + Heritage additions from AIMS Desktop 2020: python3-mpi4py,
      python3-biopython, python3-skimage, python3-igraph, python3-rpy2,
      python3-pyfftw, python3-tables, python3-pygments,
      python3-reportlab, plus texlive-lang-african (Wolof, Swahili,
      Amharic, Hausa, Twi hyphenation), texlive-lang-arabic,
      texlive-publishers, texlive-pictures, dvipng.
  * All 36 new packages confirmed available on arm64 AND amd64 in
    Trixie main.

